===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|いん|yomi=kanon}}
The senses “Shang dynasty” and “prosperous” are from {{der|ja|ltc|sort=いん|-}} {{ltc-l|殷|id=1}}, corresponding to modern Mandarin ''yīn'' and Cantonese ''jan<sup>1</sup>''. The sense “rumbling” corresponds to modern Mandarin ''yǐn'' and Cantonese ''jan<sup>2</sup>''.

The ''[[漢音#Japanese|kan'on]]'' pronunciation, so likely a later borrowing.

